<item>
            <title>[CXF-4200] UriInfoImpl.getPathSegments(decode) does not pass &apos;decode&apos; flag to getPath()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-4200</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The function &apos;UriInfoImpl.getPathSegments(boolean decode)&apos; calls &apos;getPath()&apos; internally. It should call &apos;getPath(decode)&apos; instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As an example, consider the following path: &apos;a/x%2fy/b&apos; (&apos;%2f&apos; = &apos;/&apos;).&lt;br/&gt;
When calling &apos;UriInfoImpl.getPathSegments(true)&apos;, four path segments are returned: &apos;a&apos;, &apos;x&apos;, &apos;y&apos;, &apos;b&apos;. However, when &apos;UriInfoImpl.getPathSegments(false)&apos; is called, the result is the same. Instead, &apos;a&apos;, &apos;x%2fy&apos;, &apos;b&apos; is expected.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12547820">CXF-4200</key>
