                            <comment id="13236697" author="robth" created="Fri, 23 Mar 2012 15:48:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13237256" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Fri, 23 Mar 2012 23:03:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch. I ended up always passing &apos;false&apos; to getPath() within the getPathSegments(boolean decoded) otherwise we have another bug, namely x%2Fy is treated as if it represents two PathSegments due to it containing the encoded &apos;/&apos;. The actual &apos;decode&apos; flag is passed to the PathSegment implementation.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
